urlLink Gold-Collar Workers. ERIC Digest.   This ERIC Digest is by Michael Wonacott.  It looks at the class of workers known as gold collar.  From the ERIC Digest:  What do these workers have in common: aircraft systems maintenance technicians, computer engineers, holders of a master of science in physics-entrepreneurship track, customer service representatives engaged in electronic customer relationship management, and older workers. They are all considered gold-collar workers, by one commentator or another. This Digest reviews the characteristics of gold-collar workers and identifies implications of those characteristics for employers and educators.